# Default Engineering Workflow

Follow this sequence for every story or task:

1) Update develop and branch
- `git checkout develop && git pull --ff-only`
- Create feature branch: `feat/<JIRA-KEY>-<kebab-summary>`

2) Plan → Todos → Implement
- Post a concise implementation plan as a comment on the Jira issue
- Materialize the plan into todos (track major units of work only)
- Implement step-by-step, updating todos as you go

3) Linters/Type-checks/Tests
- Run pre-commit hooks locally (black, ruff, flake8, mypy, pytest)
- Ensure pytest coverage ≥ configured threshold (see CI rule)

4) PR + CI
- Open a PR to `develop` with a clear title and checklist of acceptance criteria
- After triggering CI, wait the configured grace period before checking status

5) Merge & Next
- After merge: update local `develop`, then pick the next highest-priority Jira story in To Do

6) Minimize user interaction
- Only ask questions when information is missing or ambiguous

